title: SFH on development of public hospitals
content_text:
p>
			Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for 
			Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after attending the meeting of 
			Legislative Council Panel on Health Services this afternoon (July 
			15): Secretary for Food and Health: We have introduced to the Legislative 
			Council Panel on Health Services today a blueprint of the future 
			development of public hospitals. As Hong Kong's long-term population 
			growth as well as rapidly aging population put a huge demand on

growth as well as rapidly aging population put a huge demand on 
			public hospital facilities in the medium and long term, we have 
			decided to pursue the development of a general hospital in the Kai 
			Tak Development Area in the blueprint. Also, there would be needs 
			for additional rehabilitation hospital beds in Tai Po. Considering 
			the fact that there is still residual development potential of the 
			existing Tai Po Hospital site, and the Chinese University of Hong 
			Kong has raised with the Administration a plan to develop a private

Kong has raised with the Administration a plan to develop a private 
			teaching hospital within its campus, there is no need for our bureau 
			to hold the piece of land originally reserved for private hospital 
			development. Therefore, we have decided to return the piece of land 
			(reserved for private hospital development) in Tai Po to the 
			Development Bureau for other development purposes.  (Please also refer to the
